Isn&#x27;t this the exact argument for why C++ has namespaces? I would assume that you could easily just do the following:<p><pre><code>    void drawLine(lib1::Point, lib1::Point);

    void drawRectangle(lib2::Point, lib2::Point);
</code></pre>
In this case the usage is clear (and IIRC I think most IDE&#x27;s will avoid omitting lib1:: and lib2:: in compiled code even if you do). The whole point of namespacing is to avoid the name collision issues that are (were?) inherent to C.
